[635]{book,ch,vs,text,fn}:
  moses,1,1,"The words of God, which he spake unto Moses at a time when Moses was caught up into an exceedingly high mountain,","27:32:Alma 12:30; Moses 1:42.|104:112:Ex. 19:3; Ezek. 40:2; Rev. 21:10; Moses 1:42."
  moses,1,2,"And he saw God face to face, and he talked with him, and the glory of God was upon Moses; therefore Moses could endure his presence.","7:10:Ex. 3:6; 33:20 (11–23); John 1:18; Ether 3:15; Moses 1:11. TG God, Privilege of Seeing; Jesus Christ, Appearances, Antemortal; Vision.|15:27:Num. 12:8; Deut. 34:10; D&C 17:1. TG God, Manifestations of.|36:42:Ex. 25:1. TG Communication.|61:66:Deut. 5:24; Moses 1:14 (13–14, 25). TG Glory; God, Glory of; Transfiguration."
  moses,1,3,"And God spake unto Moses, saying: Behold, I am the Lord God Almighty, and Endless is my name; for I am without beginning of days or end of years; and is not this endless?","60:68:Rev. 19:6. TG Jesus Christ, Power of.|74:81:Isa. 63:16; D&C 19:10 (9–12); Moses 7:35. TG God, Eternal Nature of.|88:92:Ex. 3:15."
  moses,1,4,"And, behold, thou art my son; wherefore look, and I will show thee the workmanship of mine hands; but not all, for my works are without end, and also my words, for they never cease.","40:44:Moses 7:4.|71:82:Job 9:12.|91:96:Moses 7:32 (32–37).|118:123:Ps. 40:5; 92:5; Morm. 9:16 (16–20); D&C 76:114. TG God, Power of.|136:139:Ps. 111:8 (7–8); 1 Ne. 14:7; D&C 29:33; Moses 1:38.|153:158:Ps. 33:11; 2 Ne. 9:16; D&C 1:38 (37–39)."
  moses,1,5,"Wherefore, no man can behold all my works, except he behold all my glory; and no man can behold all my glory, and afterwards remain in the flesh on the earth.","36:41:TG God, Works of.|67:72:TG Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of.|89:95:TG God, Privilege of Seeing.|103:108:Ex. 24:17; John 12:41. TG Celestial Glory."
  moses,1,6,"And I have a work for thee, Moses, my son; and thou art in the similitude of mine Only Begotten; and mine Only Begotten is and shall be the Savior, for he is full of grace and truth; but there is no God beside me, and all things are present with me, for I know them all.","63:73:Gen. 1:26; Deut. 18:15; Acts 3:22; 1 Ne. 22:21; Moses 1:16 (13–16).|82:86:Moses 1:33.|87:95:Moses 6:57.|140:146:1 Ne. 13:40. TG Jesus Christ, Savior.|166:171:John 1:17 (14, 17); 2 Ne. 2:6; Alma 13:9. TG Grace.|176:181:Moses 5:7.|196:198:Deut. 32:17; 1 Kgs. 8:60; Isa. 44:8; 45:5 (5–22); 46:9.|256:260:Isa. 48:3 (3–7); 1 Ne. 9:6; Moses 1:35. TG God, Foreknowledge of; God, Omniscience of."
  moses,1,7,"And now, behold, this one thing I show unto thee, Moses, my son, for thou art in the world, and now I show it unto thee.",""
  moses,1,8,"And it came to pass that Moses looked, and beheld the world upon which he was created; and Moses beheld the world and the ends thereof, and all the children of men which are, and which were created; of the same he greatly marveled and wondered.","54:59:Moses 2:1.|97:103:Moses 1:27.|222:230:Ps. 8:3 (3–4)."
  moses,1,9,"And the presence of God withdrew from Moses, that his glory was not upon Moses; and Moses was left unto himself. And as he was left unto himself, he fell unto the earth.","8:16:Job 10:12.|54:59:TG Glory.|149:153:Isa. 6:5; Acts 9:4; JS—H 1:20."
  moses,1,10,"And it came to pass that it was for the space of many hours before Moses did again receive his natural strength like unto man; and he said unto himself: Now, for this cause I know that man is nothing, which thing I never had supposed.","103:111:Dan. 10:8 (8, 17); 1 Ne. 17:47; 19:20; Alma 27:17.|185:188:TG Mortality.|192:199:Job 42:6 (1–6); Dan. 4:35; Hel. 12:7; Ether 3:2. TG Humility."
  moses,1,11,"But now mine own eyes have beheld God; but not my natural, but my spiritual eyes, for my natural eyes could not have beheld; for I should have withered and died in his presence; but his glory was upon me; and I beheld his face, for I was transfigured before him.","27:33:Moses 1:2. TG God, Privilege of Seeing.|50:57:Moses 6:36.|66:75:Moses 1:31.|89:96:Ex. 33:20.|117:123:D&C 67:10 (10–13).|143:151:Ex. 19:21; D&C 67:11 (11–13).|156:160:Ex. 20:19.|186:191:TG Glory.|222:226:Gen. 32:30; Moses 7:4.|238:250:Matt. 17:2 (1–8); D&C 137:1. TG Transfiguration."
  moses,1,12,"And it came to pass that when Moses had said these words, behold, Satan came tempting him, saying: Moses, son of man, worship me.","66:71:Moses 4:4 (1, 4). TG Devil.|77:85:Luke 4:2 (1–13); 2 Cor. 11:14 (13–15); Rev. 12:9 (7–9); 2 Ne. 1:18 (17–18); Moses 1:21; 6:49."
  moses,1,13,"And it came to pass that Moses looked upon Satan and said: Who art thou? For behold, I am a son of God, in the similitude of his Only Begotten; and where is thy glory, that I should worship thee?","92:95:Job 1:6; Isa. 14:12 (12–15).|161:166:D&C 88:24."
  moses,1,14,"For behold, I could not look upon God, except his glory should come upon me, and I were transfigured before him. But I can look upon thee in the natural man. Is it not so, surely?","50:55:Moses 1:2 (2, 25). TG Glory.|119:122:Rev. 1:17."
  moses,1,15,"Blessed be the name of my God, for his Spirit hath not altogether withdrawn from me, or else where is thy glory, for it is darkness unto me? And I can judge between thee and God; for God said unto me: Worship God, for him only shalt thou serve.","39:45:TG God, Spirit of.|201:208:Matt. 4:10. TG Worship.|238:243:1 Sam. 7:3; 3 Ne. 13:24."
  moses,1,16,"Get thee hence, Satan; deceive me not; for God said unto me: Thou art after the similitude of mine Only Begotten.","80:90:Moses 1:6. TG God, Body of, Corporeal Nature."
  moses,1,17,"And he also gave me commandments when he called unto me out of the burning bush, saying: Call upon God in the name of mine Only Begotten, and worship me.","41:47:Ex. 19:3.|75:79:Ex. 3:2 (2–15).|89:93:Moses 5:8."
  moses,1,18,"And again Moses said: I will not cease to call upon God, I have other things to inquire of him: for his glory has been upon me, wherefore I can judge between him and thee. Depart hence, Satan.","104:109:TG Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of.|172:178:Matt. 4:10."
  moses,1,19,"And now, when Moses had said these words, Satan cried with a loud voice, and ranted upon the earth, and commanded, saying: I am the Only Begotten, worship me.","42:47:TG False Christs.|132:145:JS—M 1:6 (5–9)."
  moses,1,20,"And it came to pass that Moses began to fear exceedingly; and as he began to fear, he saw the bitterness of hell. Nevertheless, calling upon God, he received strength, and he commanded, saying: Depart from me, Satan, for this one God only will I worship, which is the God of glory.","40:44:TG Fearful.|108:112:D&C 76:47 (44–47). TG Hell.|128:135:JS—H 1:16 (15–16). TG Prayer.|158:166:TG God, Power of; Strength.|275:280:TG Glory."
  moses,1,21,"And now Satan began to tremble, and the earth shook; and Moses received strength, and called upon God, saying: In the name of the Only Begotten, depart hence, Satan.","145:151:Moses 1:12.|159:164:Matt. 10:1. TG Spirits, Evil or Unclean."
  moses,1,22,"And it came to pass that Satan cried with a loud voice, with weeping, and wailing, and gnashing of teeth; and he departed hence, even from the presence of Moses, that he beheld him not.","87:95:Matt. 13:42 (41–42); Mosiah 16:2 (1–3)."
  moses,1,23,And now of this thing Moses bore record; but because of wickedness it is not had among the children of men.,"56:66:Luke 11:52. TG Record Keeping.|73:76:Moses 1:41."
  moses,1,24,"And it came to pass that when Satan had departed from the presence of Moses, that Moses lifted up his eyes unto heaven, being filled with the Holy Ghost, which beareth record of the Father and the Son;","142:152:3 Ne. 11:32 (32, 36); Moses 8:24."
  moses,1,25,"And calling upon the name of God, he beheld his glory again, for it was upon him; and he heard a voice, saying: Blessed art thou, Moses, for I, the Almighty, have chosen thee, and thou shalt be made stronger than many waters; for they shall obey thy command as if thou wert God.","48:53:TG Glory.|97:102:Hel. 5:30; 3 Ne. 11:3.|163:169:Abr. 3:23.|218:224:Ex. 14:21.|250:257:TG Priesthood, Authority.|274:277:Ex. 4:16."
  moses,1,26,"And lo, I am with thee, even unto the end of thy days; for thou shalt deliver my people from bondage, even Israel my chosen.","13:22:TG Walking with God.|70:77:Ex. 3:10 (7–12). TG Israel, Deliverance of.|93:100:Ex. 20:2; Ps. 80:8; 1 Ne. 17:23 (23–25). TG Israel, Bondage of, in Egypt.|107:113:1 Kgs. 8:53 (51, 53). TG Israel, Twelve Tribes of.|117:123:Ps. 33:12."
  moses,1,27,"And it came to pass, as the voice was still speaking, Moses cast his eyes and beheld the earth, yea, even all of it; and there was not a particle of it which he did not behold, discerning it by the Spirit of God.","78:84:D&C 88:47 (45–47); Moses 1:8; 7:23; Abr. 3:21 (21–23). TG Vision.|177:187:TG Discernment, Spiritual; Holy Ghost, Mission of.|198:204:TG God, Spirit of."
  moses,1,28,"And he beheld also the inhabitants thereof, and there was not a soul which he beheld not; and he discerned them by the Spirit of God; and their numbers were great, even numberless as the sand upon the sea shore.","64:68:Moses 7:23."
  moses,1,29,"And he beheld many lands; and each land was called earth, and there were inhabitants on the face thereof.","51:56:Gen. 1:10. TG Earth, Dividing of.|73:84:1 Ne. 17:36."
  moses,1,30,"And it came to pass that Moses called upon God, saying: Tell me, I pray thee, why these things are so, and by what thou madest them?","56:60:Moses 2:1."
  moses,1,31,"And behold, the glory of the Lord was upon Moses, so that Moses stood in the presence of God, and talked with him face to face. And the Lord God said unto Moses: For mine own purpose have I made these things. Here is wisdom and it remaineth in me.","114:126:Deut. 5:4; Moses 1:11.|175:182:Isa. 45:18 (17–18); Eph. 3:11 (7–12); 2 Ne. 2:15 (14–30). TG Earth, Purpose of.|217:223:TG God, Intelligence of."
  moses,1,32,"And by the word of my power, have I created them, which is mine Only Begotten Son, who is full of grace and truth.","11:15:John 1:3 (1–4); Heb. 1:2 (1–3); Rev. 19:13 (13–15); Jacob 4:9; Moses 2:1 (1, 5). TG Jesus Christ, Authority of.|98:103:Moses 5:7 (7–8). TG Grace."
  moses,1,33,"And worlds without number have I created; and I also created them for mine own purpose; and by the Son I created them, which is mine Only Begotten.","4:10:Job 9:9 (7–9); Ps. 8:3 (3–4); Amos 9:6; D&C 76:24; Moses 7:30 (29–31). TG Astronomy; Creation; God, Works of; World.|33:40:TG God, Creator.|99:102:TG Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship; Jesus Christ, Jehovah.|105:112:TG Jesus Christ, Creator.|133:146:Moses 1:6."
  moses,1,34,"And the first man of all men have I called Adam, which is many.","8:13:Moses 3:7.|43:47:Abr. 1:3. TG Adam.|58:62:1 Cor. 15:45 (45–48); 2 Ne. 2:20 (19–20); D&C 27:11; 76:24; 138:38; Moses 4:26; 6:9."
  moses,1,35,"But only an account of this earth, and the inhabitants thereof, give I unto you. For behold, there are many worlds that have passed away by the word of my power. And there are many that now stand, and innumerable are they unto man; but all things are numbered unto me, for they are mine and I know them.","293:297:1 Ne. 9:6; D&C 38:2; 88:41; Moses 1:6; 7:36; Abr. 3:2 (1–16). TG God, Omniscience of."
  moses,1,36,"And it came to pass that Moses spake unto the Lord, saying: Be merciful unto thy servant, O God, and tell me concerning this earth, and the inhabitants thereof, and also the heavens, and then thy servant will be content.","101:105:Moses 2:1."
  moses,1,37,"And the Lord God spake unto Moses, saying: The heavens, they are many, and they cannot be numbered unto man; but they are numbered unto me, for they are mine.","47:54:Gen. 1:1; Moses 2:1; Abr. 4:1. TG Heaven."
  moses,1,38,"And as one earth shall pass away, and the heavens thereof even so shall another come; and there is no end to my works, neither to my words.","102:105:Moses 1:4."
  moses,1,39,"For behold, this is my work and my glory—to bring to pass the immortality and eternal life of man.","23:27:Ps. 90:16; Matt. 5:48; Rom. 8:17 (14–21); 2 Ne. 2:15 (14–30); Alma 42:26; D&C 29:43 (42–44). TG God, Works of.|35:40:Micah 2:9; Mosiah 4:12; D&C 81:4 (3–4). TG Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of.|62:73:Moses 6:59. TG Immortality; Jesus Christ, Mission of; Resurrection.|78:85:TG Eternal Life; Man, Potential to Become like Heavenly Father.|86:90:TG Earth, Purpose of."
  moses,1,40,"And now, Moses, my son, I will speak unto thee concerning this earth upon which thou standest; and thou shalt write the things which I shall speak.","110:115:Neh. 13:1 (1–3); 2 Tim. 3:16; 2 Ne. 29:11 (11–12)."
  moses,1,41,"And in a day when the children of men shall esteem my words as naught and take many of them from the book which thou shalt write, behold, I will raise up another like unto thee; and they shall be had again among the children of men—among as many as shall believe.","63:69:Moses 1:23.|74:78:1 Ne. 13:26 (23–32).|101:105:Ex. 17:14; 1 Ne. 5:11; 19:23.|162:166:2 Ne. 3:9 (7–19).|196:199:1 Ne. 13:32, 39–40; D&C 9:2."
  moses,1,42,"(These words were spoken unto Moses in the mount, the name of which shall not be known among the children of men. And now they are spoken unto you. Show them not unto any except them that believe. Even so. Amen.)","18:24:Moses 1:1."
  moses,2,1,"And it came to pass that the Lord spake unto Moses, saying: Behold, I reveal unto you concerning this heaven, and this earth; write the words which I speak. I am the Beginning and the End, the Almighty God; by mine Only Begotten I created these things; yea, in the beginning I created the heaven, and the earth upon which thou standest.","70:76:Moses 1:30 (30, 36).|102:108:TG Heaven.|119:124:Moses 1:8.|126:131:D&C 76:80. TG Record Keeping; Scribe; Scriptures, Writing of.|193:205:1 Ne. 1:14.|215:228:Moses 1:32; Abr. 4:1.|231:238:TG Creation; Jesus Christ, Creator.|277:284:TG God, Creator; God, Works of.|289:295:Gen. 1:1."
  moses,2,2,"And the earth was without form, and void; and I caused darkness to come up upon the face of the deep; and my Spirit moved upon the face of the water; for I am God.","26:30:Jer. 4:23 (23–25).|55:63:TG Darkness, Physical.|109:115:TG God, Spirit of.|116:121:Gen. 1:2; Abr. 4:2."
  moses,2,3,"And I, God, said: Let there be light; and there was light.","31:36:D&C 88:7 (6–13). TG Light [noun]."
  moses,2,4,"And I, God, saw the light; and that light was good. And I, God, divided the light from the darkness.","46:50:Gen. 1:4; Abr. 4:4.|76:81:TG Light [noun]."
  moses,2,5,"And I, God, called the light Day; and the darkness, I called Night; and this I did by the word of my power, and it was done as I spake; and the evening and the morning were the first day.","90:94:Moses 1:32.|129:134:Ps. 33:9; 2 Cor. 4:6.|183:186:Gen. 1:5."
  moses,2,6,"And again, I, God, said: Let there be a firmament in the midst of the water, and it was so, even as I spake; and I said: Let it divide the waters from the waters; and it was done;","40:49:See Abr., fac. 2, fig. 4 concerning the firmament or expanse. See also Gen. 1:6 (6–8); Moses 2:14–18."
  moses,2,7,"And I, God, made the firmament and divided the waters, yea, the great waters under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament, and it was so even as I spake.","47:53:Amos 9:6; Abr. 4:9 (9–10)."
  moses,2,8,"And I, God, called the firmament Heaven; and the evening and the morning were the second day.","33:39:IE The whole expanse around about the earth, its atmosphere, and beyond are generically here called “Heaven.” The same word is also used sometimes to refer to paradise, to the dwelling place of God, and to the kingdoms of glory."
  moses,2,9,"And I, God, said: Let the waters under the heaven be gathered together unto one place, and it was so; and I, God, said: Let there be dry land; and it was so.","26:32:TG Earth, Dividing of.|76:79:Gen. 1:9; Abr. 4:9."
  moses,2,10,"And I, God, called the dry land Earth; and the gathering together of the waters, called I the Sea; and I, God, saw that all things which I had made were good.","32:37:IE The whole sphere or any of its parts above the seas is called “Earth.”"
  moses,2,11,"And I, God, said: Let the earth bring forth grass, the herb yielding seed, the fruit tree yielding fruit, after his kind, and the tree yielding fruit, whose seed should be in itself upon the earth, and it was so even as I spake.","44:49:Gen. 1:11 (11–12); Abr. 4:11 (11–12)."
  moses,2,12,"And the earth brought forth grass, every herb yielding seed after his kind, and the tree yielding fruit, whose seed should be in itself, after his kind; and I, God, saw that all things which I had made were good;","147:151:Gen. 1:12."
  moses,2,13,And the evening and the morning were the third day.,""
  moses,2,14,"And I, God, said: Let there be lights in the firmament of the heaven, to divide the day from the night, and let them be for signs, and for seasons, and for days, and for years;","31:37:Ps. 104:19."
  moses,2,15,And let them be for lights in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth; and it was so.,""
  moses,2,16,"And I, God, made two great lights; the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light to rule the night, and the greater light was the sun, and the lesser light was the moon; and the stars also were made even according to my word.","47:52:TG Light [noun].|118:125:Gen. 1:16."
  moses,2,17,"And I, God, set them in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth,",""
  moses,2,18,"And the sun to rule over the day, and the moon to rule over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness; and I, God, saw that all things which I had made were good;","8:11:TG Astronomy.|104:112:TG Darkness, Physical."
  moses,2,19,And the evening and the morning were the fourth day.,""
  moses,2,20,"And I, God, said: Let the waters bring forth abundantly the moving creature that hath life, and fowl which may fly above the earth in the open firmament of heaven.",""
  moses,2,21,"And I, God, created great whales, and every living creature that moveth, which the waters brought forth abundantly, after their kind, and every winged fowl after his kind; and I, God, saw that all things which I had created were good.","26:32:Gen. 1:21; Abr. 4:21."
  moses,2,22,"And I, God, blessed them, saying: Be fruitful, and multiply, and fill the waters in the sea; and let fowl multiply in the earth;","51:59:Gen. 1:22 (20–25); D&C 45:58; 132:63 (55–56, 63); Abr. 4:22."
  moses,2,23,And the evening and the morning were the fifth day.,""
  moses,2,24,"And I, God, said: Let the earth bring forth the living creature after his kind, cattle, and creeping things, and beasts of the earth after their kind, and it was so;",""
  moses,2,25,"And I, God, made the beasts of the earth after their kind, and cattle after their kind, and everything which creepeth upon the earth after his kind; and I, God, saw that all these things were good.",""
  moses,2,26,"And I, God, said unto mine Only Begotten, which was with me from the beginning: Let us make man in our image, after our likeness; and it was so. And I, God, said: Let them have dominion over the fishes of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over the cattle, and over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth.","27:40:TG Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.|69:78:TG Jesus Christ, Firstborn.|84:86:TG Jesus Christ, Creator.|87:91:TG Man, Physical Creation of.|103:108:Gen. 1:26 (26–28); Moses 6:9 (8–10); Abr. 4:26 (26–31).|177:185:Gen. 1:26 (26–28); D&C 76:111 (110–12); 121:37 (34–46); Moses 5:1; Abr. 4:26 (26–28)."
  moses,2,27,"And I, God, created man in mine own image, in the image of mine Only Begotten created I him; male and female created I them.","36:41:TG God, Body of, Corporeal Nature."
  moses,2,28,"And I, God, blessed them, and said unto them: Be fruitful, and multiply, and replenish the earth, and subdue it, and have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over every living thing that moveth upon the earth.","49:57:TG Birth Control.|63:71:Moses 5:2. TG Marriage, Fatherhood."
  moses,2,29,"And I, God, said unto man: Behold, I have given you every herb bearing seed, which is upon the face of all the earth, and every tree in the which shall be the fruit of a tree yielding seed; to you it shall be for meat.","213:217:Gen. 1:29 (29–30); Ps. 136:25; D&C 104:17 (15–18); Abr. 4:29 (29–30)."
  moses,2,30,"And to every beast of the earth, and to every fowl of the air, and to everything that creepeth upon the earth, wherein I grant life, there shall be given every clean herb for meat; and it was so, even as I spake.",""
  moses,2,31,"And I, God, saw everything that I had made, and, behold, all things which I had made were very good; and the evening and the morning were the sixth day.","95:99:Gen. 1:31; Moro. 7:12; D&C 59:17 (16–20).|142:147:Ex. 20:11 (8–11); 31:17; Mosiah 13:19; Abr. 4:31."
  moses,3,1,"Thus the heaven and the earth were finished, and all the host of them.","9:15:TG Creation.|57:61:Gen. 2:1; D&C 29:36; 38:1; 45:1; Abr. 5:1."
  moses,3,2,"And on the seventh day I, God, ended my work, and all things which I had made; and I rested on the seventh day from all my work, and all things which I had made were finished, and I, God, saw that they were good;","85:91:Gen. 2:2 (1–3); Abr. 5:2 (1–3). TG Rest.|99:110:TG Sabbath."
  moses,3,3,"And I, God, blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it; because that in it I had rested from all my work which I, God, had created and made.","12:19:Ex. 20:11; Mosiah 13:19; D&C 77:12.|41:51:Abr. 5:3 (1–3).|100:104:Ex. 31:15 (14–15); Mosiah 13:18 (16–19)."
  moses,3,4,"And now, behold, I say unto you, that these are the generations of the heaven and of the earth, when they were created, in the day that I, the Lord God, made the heaven and the earth,","111:118:Gen. 2:4 (4–5); Abr. 5:4 (4–5).|162:168:Neh. 9:6."
  moses,3,5,"And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew. For I, the Lord God, created all things, of which I have spoken, spiritually, before they were naturally upon the face of the earth. For I, the Lord God, had not caused it to rain upon the face of the earth. And I, the Lord God, had created all the children of men; and not yet a man to till the ground; for in heaven created I them; and there was not yet flesh upon the earth, neither in the water, neither in the air;","122:129:Moses 6:51. TG Creation; God, Creator.|166:177:D&C 29:31–34; Abr. 3:23. TG Life, Sanctity of; Spirit Creation.|196:205:Moses 3:9. TG Man, Physical Creation of.|334:341:TG Man, a Spirit Child of Heavenly Father.|397:403:Gen. 2:5.|412:418:TG Heaven.|419:426:TG Man, Antemortal Existence of."
  moses,3,6,"But I, the Lord God, spake, and there went up a mist from the earth, and watered the whole face of the ground.","48:52:Gen. 2:6."
  moses,3,7,"And I, the Lord God, formed man from the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living soul, the first flesh upon the earth, the first man also; nevertheless, all things were before created; but spiritually were they created and made according to my word.","41:45:Gen. 2:7; Moses 4:25 (25–29); 6:59; Abr. 5:7.|96:110:TG Breath of Life.|116:119:TG Adam.|136:140:Isa. 57:16. TG Soul.|146:151:Moses 1:34."
  moses,3,8,"And I, the Lord God, planted a garden eastward in Eden, and there I put the man whom I had formed.","50:54:Isa. 51:3. TG Eden."
