  moses,4,11,"For God doth know that in the day ye eat thereof, then your eyes shall be opened, and ye shall be as gods, knowing good and evil.","60:64:Gen. 3:5 (3–6); D&C 76:12 (12, 19); Moses 5:10.|107:114:Alma 12:31. TG Knowledge."
  moses,4,12,"And when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it became pleasant to the eyes, and a tree to be desired to make her wise, she took of the fruit thereof, and did eat, and also gave unto her husband with her, and he did eat.","114:121:Gen. 3:6; 1 Ne. 8:12 (10–15); 15:36.|156:161:D&C 29:40.|179:182:TG Fall of Man."
  moses,4,13,"And the eyes of them both were opened, and they knew that they had been naked. And they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves aprons.","72:77:Gen. 2:25; 2 Ne. 9:14.|134:140:TG Apparel."
  moses,4,14,"And they heard the voice of the Lord God, as they were walking in the garden, in the cool of the day; and Adam and his wife went to hide themselves from the presence of the Lord God amongst the trees of the garden.","55:62:Gen. 3:8.|157:165:Jonah 1:3."
