  moses,4,20,"And I, the Lord God, said unto the serpent: Because thou hast done this thou shalt be cursed above all cattle, and above every beast of the field; upon thy belly shalt thou go, and dust shalt thou eat all the days of thy life;","86:92:Gen. 3:14 (13–16)."
  moses,4,21,"And I will put enmity between thee and the woman, between thy seed and her seed; and he shall bruise thy head, and thou shalt bruise his heel.","15:21:Gen. 3:15.|94:100:Ps. 68:21; Rom. 16:20; Heb. 2:14."
  moses,4,22,"Unto the woman, I, the Lord God, said: I will greatly multiply thy sorrow and thy conception. In sorrow thou shalt bring forth children, and thy desire shall be to thy husband, and he shall rule over thee.","97:103:Gen. 3:16. TG Pain.|168:175:TG Marriage, Husbands; Marriage, Wives."
