  moses,4,24,"Thorns also, and thistles shall it bring forth to thee, and thou shalt eat the herb of the field.",""
  moses,4,25,"By the sweat of thy face shalt thou eat bread, until thou shalt return unto the ground—for thou shalt surely die—for out of it wast thou taken: for dust thou wast, and unto dust shalt thou return.","7:12:Gen. 3:19 (17–19). TG Mortality.|20:24:Moses 5:1.|148:152:Gen. 2:7; Job 10:9; Ps. 104:29; Alma 42:30; Moses 3:7; 6:59; Abr. 5:7."
  moses,4,26,"And Adam called his wife's name Eve, because she was the mother of all living; for thus have I, the Lord God, called the first of all women, which are many.","151:155:Moses 1:34; 6:9."
