  moses,5,9,"And in that day the Holy Ghost fell upon Adam, which beareth record of the Father and the Son, saying: I am the Only Begotten of the Father from the beginning, henceforth and forever, that as thou hast fallen thou mayest be redeemed, and all mankind, even as many as will.","20:30:TG Holy Ghost, Baptism of.|112:125:TG Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.|202:208:TG Death, Spiritual, First; Fall of Man.|224:232:Ps. 49:15; Mosiah 27:24 (24–26); D&C 93:38; A of F 1:3. TG Redemption; Salvation, Plan of."
  moses,5,10,"And in that day Adam blessed God and was filled, and began to prophesy concerning all the families of the earth, saying: Blessed be the name of God, for because of my transgression my eyes are opened, and in this life I shall have joy, and again in the flesh I shall see God.","41:47:TG Man, New, Spiritually Reborn.|62:70:D&C 107:56 (41–56).|167:180:TG Transgress.|184:188:Gen. 3:5 (3–6); D&C 76:12 (12, 19); Moses 4:11 (10–13).|231:234:TG Joy.|253:258:Job 19:26; 2 Ne. 9:4."
  moses,5,11,"And Eve, his wife, heard all these things and was glad, saying: Were it not for our transgression we never should have had seed, and never should have known good and evil, and the joy of our redemption, and the eternal life which God giveth unto all the obedient.","123:127:2 Ne. 2:23 (22–25). TG Birth Control; Family; Marriage, Motherhood.|151:156:Gen. 3:22."
  moses,5,12,"And Adam and Eve blessed the name of God, and they made all things known unto their sons and their daughters.","13:16:Gen. 3:20; D&C 138:39.|67:72:Deut. 4:9 (9–10)."
  moses,5,13,"And Satan came among them, saying: I am also a son of God; and he commanded them, saying: Believe it not; and they believed it not, and they loved Satan more than God. And men began from that time forth to be carnal, sensual, and devilish.","4:9:TG Devil.|90:97:TG Spiritual Blindness; Unbelief.|141:146:Moses 5:28; 6:15.|209:215:TG Carnal Mind; Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn."
  moses,5,14,And the Lord God called upon men by the Holy Ghost everywhere and commanded them that they should repent;,"40:50:John 14:26 (16–26)."
  moses,5,15,"And as many as believed in the Son, and repented of their sins, should be saved; and as many as believed not and repented not, should be damned; and the words went forth out of the mouth of God in a firm decree; wherefore they must be fulfilled.","15:23:TG Faith.|74:79:TG Jesus Christ, Savior.|137:143:D&C 42:60."
  moses,5,16,"And Adam and Eve, his wife, ceased not to call upon God. And Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bare Cain, and said: I have gotten a man from the Lord; wherefore he may not reject his words. But behold, Cain hearkened not, saying: Who is the Lord that I should know him?","112:116:Gen. 4:1 (1–2).|219:228:1 Sam. 3:13; 1 Ne. 2:12 (12–13); Mosiah 27:8 (7–37).|272:276:Ex. 5:2; Alma 9:6."
  moses,5,17,"And she again conceived and bare his brother Abel. And Abel hearkened unto the voice of the Lord. And Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.","60:69:Heb. 11:4.|102:106:D&C 138:40."
  moses,5,18,"And Cain loved Satan more than God. And Satan commanded him, saying: Make an offering unto the Lord.","9:14:D&C 10:21 (20–21).|69:73:D&C 132:9 (8–11)."
  moses,5,19,And in process of time it came to pass that Cain brought of the fruit of the ground an offering unto the Lord.,"64:69:Moses 5:5."
